FBIS4-63289 "drsov098_t_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Three Coalition Ministers To Stay in Government Three Coalition Ministers To Stay in Government LD1905152494 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1400 GMT 19 May 94 LD1905152494 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network Estonian BFN [Text] Roads and Communications Minister Andi Meister, Interior Minister Heiki Arike, and Population Minister Peeter Olesk have stated that they will continue work in the government on the basis of the [1992] coalition agreement. These ERSP [Estonian National Independence Party] ministers said in a statement which they sent to the radio that they understand the need to prevent a power vacuum at a critical time for the state of Estonia. They made this decision taking into account the positions expressed at the joint meeting of the ERSP board and its Riigikogu faction.
